Use normals that belong to the two traingles that share a vertex and calculate bengind energy as $ E_{bend} = \frac 1 2 k_b \left( \hat{n}_i- \hat{n}_j \right)^2 r $, where $ k_b $ is the bending rigidity, $ r $ is edge length, and $ \hat{n}_i, \hat{n}_j $ are the normal unit vectors of the triangles meeting at the edge. the method used here is the Seung and Nelson bending energy, Seung, H. S. & Nelson, D. R. Defects in flexible membranes with crystalline order. Phys. Rev. A 38, 10051018 (1988).
